               <p>Prisoner's defence.</p>
               <p>He brought the coat into the stable, and offered to sell it; I had not money to pay for them, but offered to pay at so much a week; I went to-bed, and in the morning I found them lying there; I thought he brought them to let me have them, my mother being sick; I put them on to go to see her, and intended to be up in two or three days again.</p>
